'''Householder Franchise''' or ''census suffrage'' is where a homeowner has the right to vote in an [[election]].   This is a limited form of [[suffrage]], but different from [[equal voting]] because, to borrow a dictum, householder franchise is ''one Household, one vote'' because it entitles '''only''' the householder one vote.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}

